==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Linsang
<hw>Lin*sang"</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n*s⟦aum⟧ng")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any viverrine mammal of the genus
<gen>Prionodon</gen>, inhabiting the East Indies and Southern Asia. The
common East Indian linsang (<spn>Prionodon gracilis</spn>) is white,
crossed by broad, black bands. The Guinea linsang (<spn>Porana
Richardsonii</spn>) is brown with black spots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Linseed</ent>⟦br⟧
